Mensuration Formulae (3D shapes)
Shape
Surface Area (cm2 or m2)
Volume (cm3 or m3 or Litres)
Cuboid
TSA = 2 (lb + bh + hl)
LSA = 2h (l + b)
(or area of 4 walls)
V = l b h
l = length, b = breadth h = height
Cube
TSA = 6a2
Area of 4 walls = 4a2
V = a3
a = length of a side of the cube
Right Circular Cylinder
CSA = 2 rh
TSA = 2r (h + r)
V = r2h
r = radius of base,
h = height
Right Circular Cone
CSA = rl
TSA = r (l + r)
l2 = h2 + r2
V =
r2h
r = radius of base,
h = height &
l = slant height.
Sphere
TSA = CSA = 4r2
V =
r3
r = radius
Hemi-sphere
CSA = 2r2
TSA = 3r2
V =
r3
Frustum
CSA = (r + R) l
TSA = (r + R) l + r2 + R2
l2 = h2 + (R - r)2
V =
(r2 + R2 + rR) h
r = radius of top
R = radius of bottom
l = slant height
h = height
1 m = 100 cm
1 km = 1000 m
1 m2 = 100 x 100 cm2 = 104 cm2
1 m3 = 100 x 100 x 100 cm3 = 106 cm3
1 m3 = 1000 L = 1 Kilo litres
1 L = 1000 cm3 or 1000 c.c.
